   Nationwide Training Programs
   Training Programs | Curriculum Areas | Cities
   Course Samplers | Core Competencies
   Faculty Openings | Certificate Programs

   The Graduate School offers daytime courses in more than 100 cities
   nationwide through our seven regional training centers and the
   Government Audit Training Institute. Evening and weekend classes are
   offered in Washington, DC only.
     * Government Audit Training Institute -- Worldwide auditing courses
     * Midwest Training Center -- Serves IL, IN, IA, KS, MI, MN, MO, NE,
       ND, OH, SD, and WI
     * National Capital Training Center -- Serves the Washington, DC Metro
       Area
     * Northeast Training Center -- Serves CT, DE, ME, MD, MA, NH, NJ, NY,
       PA, PR, RI, VT, WV, Europe and the Virgin Islands
     * Pacific Training Center -- Serves HI, Asia, and the Pacific Rim
     * Southeast Training Center -- Serves AL, FL, GA, KY, MS, NC, SC, TN,
       and VA
     * Southwest Training Center -- Serves AR, CO, LA, MT, NM, OK, TX, UT,
       WY, and Panama
     * Western Training Center -- Serves AK, AZ, CA, ID, NV, OR, and WA

   Directions and locations for these centers and some of the cities where
   they offer training may be found by clicking on the center above or
   going to the Visitor Center.

